I have a really basic question. :grimacing: I'm definitely not a developer.
My client purchased a template for a pricing page. <https://www.ostendio.com/pricing-mock-up?hs_preview=dVWrlnlj-77165174594>
Annoyingly I can't change the font sizes in the editor and I can't edit the template. I want to make the the element .single-pricing .pricing-head just a tiny bit smaller so all the prices fit on one line.
Is there an easy way to do this? Help!!
Hey <@U03SVDFK9BP> you should create a child theme
So I just create a child theme and change the size of that element?
Thank you! That was easier than I thought.

Is there any way to display alt text on feature images and images in the body of pages or blog posts like captions?

I have clients that are posting news articles and are news type outlets that we have been moving onto the platform and there is so much to love about HubSpot some of the simple things like images captions you can do in Wordpress really puts a damper on things moving to this platform.

Any thoughts on displaying alt text?
